    "updated_at": "2016-12-18T04:51:16Z",
    "body": "> broken on Windows\r\n\r\n* Doesn't handle nested optionals correctly so common modules like `electron-installer-dmg` don't work on windows\r\n* Leaves native module install folders behind when they fail to install so tools like `electron-rebuild` (that uses `npm rebuild`) will fail as there appears to be a module there when there shouldn't be\r\n\r\n^^ Those are the two major blockers which I've come across"
